      <p class="paragraph__Paragraph-sc-1a1s3b3-0 jSngqc">
        You won't need to install any node modules or Sass compilers for a
        static site; you can use the built CSS. The best thing to do is to
        <a
          color="blue.5"
          href="https://unpkg.com/@primer/css/dist/primer.css"
          class="Link-kudw2l-0 fXZrkv"
          >download the built CSS</a
        >
        from the
        <a color="blue.5" href="https://unpkg.com" class="Link-kudw2l-0 fXZrkv"
          >unpkg.com</a
        >
        and host it yourself. If that's not an option, you can include a CDN
        link in your HTML:
      </p>
